<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND
        RINGS REMOVAL &#38; REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS REMOVAL &#38; REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <para>Remove the following:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Glow Plug Harness and Controller</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Lines (Low Pressure)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Pump (w/High Pressure Lines)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Intake Manifold</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Valley Pan and Gaskets</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Exhaust Manifolds</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil Dipstick</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Nozzles</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cylinder Heads</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil Pan</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>Refer to the appropriate manual section for detailed disassembly procedures.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft to position the journals for removal of the connecting rod
                    assemblies,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350509">5.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>IF A CARBON RIDGE IS NOTICED AT THE TOP OF THE CYLINDER BORE, REMOVE WITH A RAZOR KNIFE,
                            PRIOR TO REMOVING PISTON ASSEMBLY. DO NOT USE A RIDGE REAMER.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two connecting rod retaining nuts.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use a power wrench for removing connecting rod nuts. Such practice may cause
                            seizure of the connecting rod nut or bolt threads.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>INSTALL THE ALUMINUM CONNECTING ROD GUIDE PROTECTOR CAPS ZTSE4153 OVER THE CONNECTING ROD
                            BOLTS. THIS PREVENTS DAMAGE TO THE CRANKSHAFT JOURNALS (FIGURE
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350510">5.10</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cap and push the connecting rod and piston assemblies from the cylinder bore,
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350510">5.10</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350511">5.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Replace the cap and the bearing inserts on the rod so the identification codes match. Identify the
                    connecting rods and piston assemblies upon removal so they can be reinstalled in their respective
                    cylinders.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use care when removing piston assembly to prevent component damage.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350509" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11116" filename="../figcg1/cg11116.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.9 Positioning Connecting Rods for Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350510" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12353a" filename="../figcg1/cg12353a.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.10 Connecting Rod Cap Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350511" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11119" filename="../figcg1/cg11119.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.11 Connecting Rod and Piston Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the piston rings
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>(
                    <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_81.xml" xrefid="ef4350501">5.1</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) using a piston ring expander. Remove the top compression ring first then the remaining rings in
                    order.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
